title: For Sale/Trade:  1895 Chilean Mauser 7mm, Loewe Berlin Contract Model.
postcontent: Up for sale or trade, I have a Chilean Mauser manufactured in 1895. It was a contract model made by Ludwig Loewe/DWM (Deutsche Waffen und Munitionsfabriken), in Berlin. The stock is from 1887. It is the first major modification of the Mauser Model 1893. The Model 1895 was also deployed to republic of the Orange Free State and the South African Republic, aside from it's main use by the Chilean Army. It features a surprisingly crisp bolt and trigger and fires a very capable round that was popular with elephant hunters. The rifle is 121 years old. The magazine floorplate is jammed shut and I have left it that way to avoid causing any harm to the integrity of the rifle. Email, or text me with any offers or questions.

title: For Sale:  CCW TRAINING-ALL INCLUSIVE-$60
postcontent: Armed Citizen CCW Training Schedule  Hey guys here is the upcoming CCW training calendar for the next 6 weeks. Sunday, September 25th Saturday, October 1st Saturday, October 15th Sunday, October 23rd All classes are from 9-5:30 and cost just $60. We provide everything including use of guns, ammo, range fees, student books you can keep, ear and eye protection. All you need is a photo id!  I have received a ton of questions regarding SB656 and I'm in the process of putting together a free Q&A at the store here in the near future. I will also be posting updates on FB over the coming days and weeks. First, the "constitutional carry" part of the bill does not go into effect until January 2017. Whether you plan on pursuing your permit or not I absolutely recommend you take a concealed carry training course. The certificate does not expire so you can get the training and later if you decide to apply for a permit you are good to go. Here are just some of the benefits to getting a permit *Reciprocity with other states-you will need a permit to carry out of state *Where you can carry-there are 17 prohibited places you cannot carry in Missouri. Most of these can just ask you to leave if you have a permit. Without a permit, carrying concealed in these places will be a Class B Misdemeanor *Cover your ***- The first thing a prosecutor will look at if you are involved in a defensive gun use is if you had a permit and if you had any formal training * YOU NEED TO LEARN THE LAW- where you can carry, when you can use deadly force, interacting with law enforcement, etc. This information can be hard to find and even harder to understand.  *More training never hurt anyone. I have qualified over 2k people for concealed carry alone and without fail the blowhards who act like they can't learn anything are always the ones who barely pass the live fire qualification. The most successful people in any sport are those who are open to learning and always training to be better.  This bill still needs to have the final touches on it and I will update the page as more changes become available and we have a better understanding of the bill. Do not rely on local news to accurately report this bill. IT DOES NOT MEAN THAT ANYONE CAN CONCEAL CARRY ANYWHERE THEY WANT!!! So for those of you who are already carrying please try to educate your friends and family. It is up to each and everyone of us to keep the bad apples from running the bunch with this deal. If they need training please refer them to a qualified instructor who will steer them in the right direction. As always, stay alert, be safe and TRAIN TRAIN TRAIN.
